Exploratory Text Data Analysis

People are spending an increasing amount of time on their mobile devices as 2015 reports show. Enhancement of the manipulation/typing on the mobile devices is of a tremendous use. SwiftKey company, builds a smart keyboard that makes it easier for people to type on their mobile devices. One cornerstone of their smart keyboard is predictive text models.

We are provided with the text data from a corpus called HC Corpora. We perform text mining and exploratory analysis of the data set understanding the distribution of words and relationship between the words in the corpora.

We have built a basic n-gram model for the sample of data provided, it is used for predicting the next word based on the previous 1, 2 or 3 words in the input. The model handles unseen word sequences in the corpora as well - in some cases people will want to type a combination of words that does not appear in the corpora. To build a model to handle cases where a particular n-gram isnt observed we use the Katzs back-off model reducing the n-gram size until n-gram is either found or predicting a most frequent term otherwise.
